Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer in the seventh inning.
The Los Angeles Dodgers scored three more runs in the seventh inning to beat the San Diego Padres 7-2.
Freddie Freeman left the game after an apparent injury during the seventh inning.
The Dodgers clinched the NL West title with this victory.
A sellout crowd of 52,433, including retired Dodgers star Manny Ramirez, attended the game.
Joe Musgrove pitched six shutout innings for the Padres before the Dodgers' rally.
Shohei Ohtani singled, contributing to the Dodgers' scoring in the seventh inning.
Andy Pages hit a two-run homer in the eighth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts expressed pride in his team's resilience and ability to overcome adversity.
Shohei Ohtani expressed happiness about clinching the title.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers had not clinched at home since the pandemic-shortened 2020 season.
The last time fans were present for a home clincher was in 2018.
Others: Dodgers' RHP Brusdar Graterol went on IL with right shoulder inflammation.
SS Miguel Rojas had an MRI that showed a torn adductor and will sit out the next couple of days.
LHP Anthony Banda was activated off IL.
RHP Brent Honeywell Jr. was placed on IL with a cracked right middle fingernail.
